spec: struct_extra158
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(struct)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/struct.html — Python struct module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Modules/_struct.c"
    - "CPython source: Lib/struct.py"
    - "struct_extra157.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct.__repr__.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.__repr__') / Struct.__sizeof__.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.__sizeof__') / Struct.__repr__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') / Struct.__sizeof__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method_descriptor') / qualname lengths 15 and 17 / struct.__name__/__package__ / Struct.__name__/__module__ (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra156.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct.__doc__ and struct module __doc__ type/length / struct.__doc__.__len__()==1278 / Struct.__doc__.__len__()==40 / pack_into.__name__.__eq__('pack_into') / unpack_from.__name__.__eq__('unpack_from') (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra155.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct getset_descriptor qualnames and names / Struct.size/__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.size') / Struct.format/__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.format') / calcsize/__name__ string (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra154.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct method qualnames: Struct.pack/__qualname__ / Struct.unpack/__qualname__ / Struct.pack_into/__qualname__ / Struct.pack.__class__.__name__.__eq__('method_descriptor') (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra153.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.Struct.__init__.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.__init__') / Struct.__init__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') / Struct.__doc__.__len__()==40 / error.__doc__ NoneType (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra151.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.__all__.__class__.__name__ / __all__.__contains__('pack'/'error') / __all__.__len__()==8 / error.__name__.__eq__('error') / error.__module__.__eq__('struct') / error.__qualname__.__eq__('error') / pack/__unpack/__calcsize qualnames (table + invariants)."
    - "struct_extra152.zspec.zsdl — covers struct.iter_unpack/__class__/__module__/__name__ / Struct.__name__.__len__()==6 / pack/__unpack/__calcsize/__pack_into __name__ and lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "struct.zspec / early extras — cover struct.__name__/__package__ (base spec)."
  notes:
    - "This spec does NOT duplicate invariants present in struct_extra93 through struct_extra157."
    - "Wave 344 theme: struct.Struct.__new__ and __str__ dunder qualnames; struct.error class identity — Struct.__new__.__qualname__.__eq__('Struct.__new__') / Struct.__new__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('builtin_function_or_method') / Struct.__str__.__qualname__.__eq__('object.__str__') / Struct.__str__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('wrapper_descriptor') / error.__class__.__name__.__eq__('type') / error.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('Exception')."
    - "struct.Struct.__new__.__qualname__ == 'Struct.__new__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__new__.__class__.__name__ == 'builtin_function_or_method'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__str__.__qualname__ == 'object.__str__'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__str__.__class__.__name__ == 'wrapper_descriptor'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.error.__class__.__name__ == 'type'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.error.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'Exception'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__new__.__qualname__.__len__() == 14. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.Struct.__str__.__qualname__.__len__() == 14. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "struct.error.__bases__[0].__module__ == 'builtins'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.__new__.__qualname__ == 'Struct.__new__' (14 chars = 'Struct.'=7 + '__new__'=7). Struct.__new__ is a builtin_function_or_method (not a wrapper_descriptor like __init__). '__new__' (7 chars) = '__'=2 + 'new'=3 + '__'=2. 'Struct.__new__' (14 chars) ties 'Struct.__str__' (14 chars; inherited from object). Extra157 anchors 'Struct.__repr__' (15 chars) and 'Struct.__sizeof__' (17 chars); this spec anchors 'Struct.__new__' (14 chars; shorter than __repr__) and 'Struct.__str__' (14 chars; ties __new__)."
    - "Note: struct.Struct.__str__.__qualname__ == 'object.__str__' (14 chars = 'object.'=7 + '__str__'=7). Struct.__str__ is NOT defined on Struct itself; it is inherited from the built-in object class. Therefore its __qualname__ is 'object.__str__' (with 'object.' prefix, not 'Struct.' prefix). This contrasts with __repr__ which has qualname 'Struct.__repr__' (extra157 anchors this) indicating Struct defines its own __repr__. __str__ is a wrapper_descriptor (same class type as object's special methods). 'object.__str__' (14 chars) ties 'Struct.__new__' (14 chars)."
    - "Note: struct.error.__class__.__name__ == 'type' (4 chars). struct.error is a class (a Python exception class), so its __class__ is the metaclass 'type'. This is distinct from struct.error.__name__ == 'error' (the class name itself; extra151 anchors this). struct.error inherits from Exception (struct.error.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'Exception'). struct.error.__module__ == 'struct' (extra151 anchors this). error.__class__.__name__ == 'type' confirms that struct.error is a regular Python exception class, not a C type."
    - "Note: struct.error.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'Exception' (9 chars). struct.error directly inherits from the built-in Exception class. struct.error.__bases__ is a tuple with one element: Exception. Exception is in the 'builtins' module (struct.error.__bases__[0].__module__ == 'builtins'). The inheritance chain is: struct.error -> Exception -> BaseException -> object. extra153 anchors error.__doc__==None; extra151 anchors error.__name__=='error' and error.__module__=='struct'; this spec anchors the base class identity."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

